#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.132"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.132:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.132:0.2"
msgid "13. Kusināravagga "
msgstr "13. Kusināra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.132:0.3"
msgid "132. Lekhasutta "
msgstr "132. Etchings "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.132:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these three people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.3"
msgid "Pāsāṇalekhūpamo puggalo, pathavilekhūpamo puggalo, udakalekhūpamo puggalo. "
msgstr "A person like a line drawn in stone, a person like a line drawn in sand, and a person like a line drawn in water. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.132:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, pāsāṇalekhūpamo puggalo? "
msgstr "And who is the person like a line drawn in stone? "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati. "
msgstr "It’s a person who is often angry, "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.6"
msgid "So ca khvassa kodho dīgharattaṃ anuseti. "
msgstr "and their anger lingers for a long time. "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, pāsāṇe lekhā na khippaṃ lujjati vātena vā udakena vā, ciraṭṭhitikā hoti; "
msgstr "It’s like a line drawn in stone, which isn’t quickly worn away by wind and water, but lasts for a long time. "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.8"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati. "
msgstr "In the same way, this person is often angry, "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.9"
msgid "So ca khvassa kodho dīgharattaṃ anuseti. "
msgstr "and their anger lingers for a long time. "

msgctxt "an3.132:1.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, pāsāṇalekhūpamo puggalo. "
msgstr "This is called a person like a line drawn in stone. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.132:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, pathavilekhūpamo puggalo? "
msgstr "And who is the person like a line drawn in sand? "

msgctxt "an3.132:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati. "
msgstr "It’s a person who is often angry, "

msgctxt "an3.132:2.3"
msgid "So ca khvassa kodho na dīgharattaṃ anuseti. "
msgstr "but their anger doesn’t linger long. "

msgctxt "an3.132:2.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, pathaviyā lekhā khippaṃ lujjati vātena vā udakena vā, na ciraṭṭhitikā hoti; "
msgstr "It’s like a line drawn in sand, which is quickly worn away by wind and water, and doesn’t last long. "

msgctxt "an3.132:2.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo abhiṇhaṃ kujjhati. "
msgstr "In the same way, this person is often angry, "

msgctxt "an3.132:2.6"
msgid "So ca khvassa kodho na dīgharattaṃ anuseti. "
msgstr "but their anger doesn’t linger long. "

msgctxt "an3.132:2.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, pathavilekhūpamo puggalo. "
msgstr "This is called a person like a line drawn in sand. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.284, sc3
msgctxt "an3.132:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, udakalekhūpamo puggalo? "
msgstr "And who is the person like a line drawn in water? "

#. VAR: sandhiyatimeva → … yeva (s1-3, km) | … ceva (pts1)
#. VAR: saṃsandatimeva → … yeva (s1-3, km) | … ceva (pts1)
#. VAR: sammodatimeva → … yeva (s1-3, km) | … ceva (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.132:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo āgāḷhenapi vuccamāno pharusenapi vuccamāno amanāpenapi vuccamāno sandhiyatimeva saṃsandatimeva sammodatimeva. "
msgstr "It’s a person who, though spoken to by someone in a rough, harsh, and disagreeable manner, still stays in touch, interacts with, and greets them. "

msgctxt "an3.132:3.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, udake lekhā khippaṃyeva paṭivigacchati, na ciraṭṭhitikā hoti; "
msgstr "It’s like a line drawn in water, which vanishes right away, and doesn’t last long. "

msgctxt "an3.132:3.4"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo āgāḷhenapi vuccamāno pharusenapi vuccamāno amanāpenapi vuccamāno sandhiyatimeva saṃsandatimeva sammodatimeva. "
msgstr "In the same way, this person, though spoken to by someone in a rough, harsh, and disagreeable manner, still stays in touch, interacts with, and greets them. "

msgctxt "an3.132:3.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, udakalekhūpamo puggalo. "
msgstr "This is called a person like a line drawn in water. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.132:3.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the three people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.132:3.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.132:3.8"
msgid "Kusināravaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.132:4.1"
msgid "Kusinārabhaṇḍanā ceva, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.132:4.2"
msgid "Gotamabharaṇḍuhatthako; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.132:4.3"
msgid "Kaṭuviyaṃ dve anuruddhā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.132:4.4"
msgid "Paṭicchannaṃ lekhena te dasāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
